Below is one way to “read off” the two structures from the images and match them block‐for‐block (without rotating any dictionary piece):

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  DESCRIPTION OF THE MAIN (TARGET) IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

•  There are two separate builds:

  A)  LEFT‐HAND BUILD
     –  Layers & Count:
        1)  Base Layer: Two short yellow rectangular blocks side‐by‐side (forming an “L” shape).  
        2)  Second Layer: One red arch‐shaped block (with a half‐circle cutout) resting on the left yellow block.  
        3)  Third Layer: One short green rectangular block on top of the red arch.  
        4)  Top Layer: Two blue cubes side by side on top of the green block.  
        –  Additionally, on the right‐side yellow block (the “L” part of the base) is one small orange wedge “roof” piece.

  B)  RIGHT‐HAND BUILD
     –  Layers & Count (from bottom to top):
        1)  Center/Bottom: One tall red “ring” block (the large circular hole through the middle).
        2)  Either side of that ring at the bottom: Two orange wedges (one on each side) making a wide triangular base.
        3)  Above the ring: A smaller red arch block (oriented so that its half‐circle is not seen from the front).
        4)  On top of that red piece: Two yellow half‐cylinders lying side‐by‐side.
        5)  Very Top: Two orange wedge blocks forming a peaked “roof.”

•  In total there are 15 blocks:  
   –  7 in the left‐hand tower  
   –  8 in the right‐hand “ring‐and‐roof” structure.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING THE CORRECT DICTIONARY BLOCKS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Using the exact orientations shown in the block‐dictionary (no re‐orienting):

•  LEFT BUILD needs:
  –  #7 (yellow short rectangle) × 2  
  –  #1 (red arch with half‐circle) × 1  
  –  #5 (green short rectangle) × 1  
  –  #4 (blue cube) × 2  
  –  #14 (orange wedge) × 1  

•  RIGHT BUILD needs:
  –  #3 (red ring with large circular hole) × 1  
  –  #1 (red arch) × 1  
  –  #9 (yellow half‐cylinder) × 2  
  –  #13 (orange wedge) × 1  
  –  #14 (orange wedge) × 1  
  –  #15 (orange wedge) × 1  
  –  #16 (orange wedge) × 1  

Note that some wedges (13–16) differ only by their “built‐in” orientation in the dictionary; you must pick each exactly as shown so that their slopes match the final build.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY SEQUENCE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Below is one possible order (you can of course group left‐build steps first, then the right‐build):

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 7      (place first yellow base on the left)
  Step2:  Move block with index 7      (place second yellow base on the left)
  Step3:  Move block with index 1      (red arch onto left yellow block)
  Step4:  Move block with index 5      (green rectangular block on top of red arch)
  Step5:  Move block with index 4      (first blue cube on top)
  Step6:  Move block with index 4      (second blue cube on top)
  Step7:  Move block with index 14     (orange wedge “roof” on the right side of left build)
  Step8:  Move block with index 3      (red ring for the right‐hand build)
  Step9:  Move block with index 13     (orange wedge at bottom left side of ring)
  Step10: Move block with index 14     (orange wedge at bottom right side of ring)
  Step11: Move block with index 1      (red arch on top of the ring)
  Step12: Move block with index 9      (first yellow half‐cylinder on top)
  Step13: Move block with index 9      (second yellow half‐cylinder next to it)
  Step14: Move block with index 15     (front orange wedge for the roof peak)
  Step15: Move block with index 16     (rear orange wedge for the roof peak)
}

That completes the two‐part structure exactly as shown.
